# Root .dockerignore — applies to every image whose build context is the repo
# root (apps/indexer/Dockerfile, apps/api/Dockerfile; see prod-images.md).
# Keeps the context lean and reproducible: ship manifests + lockfile +
# source; NEVER ship host node_modules (linux-native binaries are rebuilt inside
# the image), build caches, secrets, or contract/frontend artifacts.

# ── Dependencies (rebuilt in-image by pnpm; host copies are macOS-native) ─────
**/node_modules

# ── VCS / editor / OS cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore
.githooks
.github
.idea
.vscode
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log

# ── Secrets & local env (interpolated at deploy by Komodo, never baked in) ────
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# ── Frontend build output (apps/web deploys to Cloudflare Workers, not here) ──
**/.next
apps/web/.open-next

# ── Ponder local cache (regenerated; ponder-env.d.ts is (re)made by codegen) ──
**/.ponder

# ── Foundry / contract build artifacts (not needed by the off-chain images) ──
contracts/out
contracts/cache
contracts/broadcast
contracts/lib

# ── Local dev stack scratch / object-store data ──────────────────────────────
tools/localstack/out
.docker-data

# ── Test coverage & the non-authoritative bun lockfile (pnpm-lock.yaml wins) ─
**/coverage
bun.lock

# ── Docs are not build inputs for the runtime images ─────────────────────────
docs
